    "hc_tab_content_highlights_U6AUr3": {
      "type": "hc-tab-content-highlights",
      "blocks": {
        "sheets_for_men_ihWnyx": {
          "type": "sheets-for-men",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "We created the best sheets for men.",
            "subheading": "Most sheets were designed for everyone.",
            "subheading_line2": "These were designed for you.",
            "description": "Men's bodies operate differently. Higher body temperatures, sweatier nights, and less frequent washing than most bedding was ever built to handle. We took all of that into consideration when creating the Jax Sheets.",
            "cta_text": "Get to know the technology before you experience the difference.",
            "scroll_target": "self-cleaning",
            "bg_color": "#000000",
            "heading_color": "#ffffff",
            "accent_color": "#b45309",
            "description_color": "#9ca3af"
          }
        },
        "self_cleaning_qVCVyj": {
          "type": "self-cleaning",
          "settings": {
            "tag": "01 — Biologically Clean",
            "heading": "SELF-CLEANING FABRIC?",
            "description": "<p>Yes, the Jax Sheets are woven with a permanent <strong>Silver Grid</strong> that continuously inhibits the growth of bacteria, fungi, and odor-causing microbes across the entire surface.<br/>Unlike conventional bedding that passively accumulates what your body sheds through the night, the silver ions are constantly active against the microbes that thrive in warm, humid bedding environments. This keeps the fabric genuinely cleaner between washes and makes it a more hygienic environment for your skin over the long term.</p>",
            "badge_text": "99.9% Bacteria Neutralized",
            "footer_text": "Anti-Microbial Barrier Analysis",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "tooltip_trigger": "Silver Grid",
            "tooltip_content": "<p><strong>What is it?</strong></p><p>A silver grid is a network of ultra-fine silver threads woven directly into the fabric at precise intervals, forming a continuous grid structure throughout the textile. Unlike silver ion treatments that are applied to the surface of a fabric and degrade with washing, a woven silver grid is a permanent part of the sheet's construction. It does not wash out, fade, or lose effectiveness over time.</p><p><strong>Why is it in the Jax Sheets?</strong></p><p>Silver is one of the most effective natural antimicrobial elements known, and in the Jax Sheets it works continuously to inhibit the growth of bacteria, fungi, and odor-causing microbes across the entire surface of the fabric. Because the silver is woven in rather than coated on, its protective properties remain consistent wash after wash and year after year. The result is a sheet that maintains a genuinely hygienic sleep surface over the long term, without relying on chemical treatments or needing to be replaced to stay effective.</p>",
            "bg_color": "#ffffff",
            "text_color": "#000000",
            "accent_color": "#b45309",
            "desc_color": "#4b5563"
          }
        },
        "sweat_management_kdKdUp": {
          "type": "sweat-management",
          "settings": {
            "tag": "02 — Active Temperature Regulation",
            "heading": "Advanced Night Sweat Management",
            "description": "<p>Standard sheets trap heat against your skin, which forces your body to sweat in order to cool itself down and ultimately disrupts your sleep. The Jax Sheets address <strong>Phase Changing Materials</strong> embedded in the fabric that absorb excess heat as your body temperature rises, storing it within the material rather than letting it build up against your skin. As your temperature naturally drops through the night, the PCM releases that stored heat back gradually, keeping your thermal environment stable in both directions. By reducing the heat spikes that trigger night sweats in the first place, these sheets help you stay in the ideal thermal zone for uninterrupted rest.</p>",
            "badge_text": "NASA TECH",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "tooltip_trigger": "Phase Changing Materials",
            "tooltip_content": "<p><strong>What are PCMs?</strong></p><p>Physically, Phase Changing Materials are specialized, plant based waxes contained within millions of microscopic bubbles embedded in the fabric. These micro capsules allow the wax to change from a solid to a liquid and back again to manage heat, all without making the fabric feel wet or heavy. Because they are part of the fiber itself, they provide a physical temperature solution that will not wash out or lose effectiveness over time.</p><p><strong>Why are they in the JAX Sheets?</strong></p><p>We use PCMs as a thermal battery to help reduce night sweats before they start. While standard sheets only react once you are already sweating, PCMs are proactive. When you get too warm, the micro capsules absorb and store your excess body heat. When you cool down, they release it back gradually. This technology was originally developed for NASA spacesuits to help protect astronauts from extreme temperature swings. In the Jax Sheets, it works the same way, helping you maintain a more stable thermal environment throughout the night for deeper, more uninterrupted sleep.</p>",
            "bg_color": "#000000",
            "text_color": "#ffffff",
            "accent_color": "#b45309",
            "desc_color": "#9ca3af"
          }
        },
        "acne_shield_cpnML4": {
          "type": "acne-shield",
          "settings": {
            "tag": "03 — Clinical-Grade Germ Protection",
            "heading": "THE ANTI-ACNE SHIELD",
            "description": "<p>Most sleep acne is caused by bacteria that accumulate on your pillowcase and transfer back to your skin while you sleep. The <strong>Silver Grid</strong> woven into the Jax Sheets continuously inhibits the growth of those bacteria on the fabric surface, meaning your face rests on a significantly cleaner environment every night.<br/>For skin prone to breakouts, conventional pillowcases offer no protection against bacterial buildup between washes. The Jax Sheets work against it constantly.</p>",
            "card_title": "MICROBIOME PROTECTION",
            "stat_value": "99.9%",
            "stat_unit": "Kill Rate",
            "stat_title": "Bacteria Neutralization",
            "stat_desc": "Destroys acne-causing microbes every 180 seconds.",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "style_preset": "default",
            "html_id": "",
            "enable_section_animation": false,
            "tooltip_trigger": "Silver Grid",
            "tooltip_content": "<p><strong>What is it?</strong></p><p>A silver grid is a network of ultra-fine silver threads woven directly into the fabric at precise intervals, forming a continuous grid structure throughout the textile. Unlike silver ion treatments that are applied to the surface of a fabric and degrade with washing, a woven silver grid is a permanent part of the sheet's construction. It does not wash out, fade, or lose effectiveness over time.</p><p><strong>Why is it in the Jax Sheets?</strong></p><p>Silver is one of the most effective natural antimicrobial elements known, and in the Jax Sheets it works continuously to inhibit the growth of bacteria, fungi, and odor-causing microbes across the entire surface of the fabric. Because the silver is woven in rather than coated on, its protective properties remain consistent wash after wash and year after year. The result is a sheet that maintains a genuinely hygienic sleep surface over the long term, without relying on chemical treatments or needing to be replaced to stay effective.</p>",
            "tooltip_position": "center",
            "bg_color": "#ffffff",
            "text_color": "#000000",
            "accent_color": "#b45309",
            "desc_color": "#4b5563"
          }
        },
        "micron_finish_Y6FpyY": {
          "type": "micron-finish",
          "settings": {
            "tag": "04 — Softer Than Silk, Stronger Than Cotton",
            "heading": "10 Micron Finish",
            "description": "<p>Jax Sheets are engineered with 10-<strong>micron</strong> ultra-fine fibers—roughly 1/10th the thickness of a human hair. This microscopic precision creates a surface that is noticeably softer than traditional silk while maintaining the structural strength of high-performance gear. Unlike standard cotton, which features microscopic \"hooks\" that can cause texture changes over time, Jax fibers are designed for long-term smoothness.</p>",
            "card_title": "SURFACE FRICTION COEFFICIENT",
            "bar_1_label": "Cotton",
            "bar_2_label": "Silk",
            "bar_3_label": "HercLeón",
            "chart_footer": "Lower value indicates smoother surface & less skin irritation",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "tooltip_trigger": "micron",
            "tooltip_content": "<p><strong>What is it?</strong></p><p>A micron (or micrometer) is a unit of measurement equal to one-millionth of a meter. To put that in perspective, a single human hair is typically between 70 and 100 microns thick.</p><p><strong>Why does it matter for Jax Sheets?</strong></p><p>At 10 microns, our fibers are significantly finer than the threads used in standard cotton sheets. This ultra-fine diameter is the secret to our extra smooth feel; by using fibers this small, we can create a fabric surface that is microscopically dense and smooth, reducing the physical friction that causes skin irritation and hair frizz. It allows the sheets to feel as soft as luxury silk while maintaining the durability of technical performance gear.</p>",
            "bg_color": "#000000",
            "text_color": "#ffffff",
            "accent_color": "#b45309",
            "desc_color": "#9ca3af"
          }
        },
        "longevity_designed_kmHXjJ": {
          "type": "longevity-designed",
          "settings": {
            "tag": "05 — Resists Wear and Breakdown",
            "heading": "DESIGNED FOR LONGEVITY",
            "description": "<p>Frequent laundering is the primary cause of fabric wear. The friction and high heat of heavy bedding cycles eventually break down fibers, leading to stretching and thinning. Because Jax Sheets require significantly fewer washes, they avoid this routine damage. Built with a highly pill-resistant HercLeón™ structure, they are designed to maintain their performance for years—reducing textile waste and the need for frequent replacements.</p>",
            "card_title": "AVERAGE SHEET LIFESPAN",
            "standard_label": "TRADITIONAL COTTON / LINEN / POLY",
            "standard_value": "2 - 3 YEARS",
            "jax_label": "JAX SHEETS",
            "jax_value": "UP TO 10 YEARS",
            "stat_value": "5x",
            "stat_label": "Durability Factor",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "column_divider_side": "auto",
            "tooltip_trigger": "",
            "tooltip_content": "",
            "bg_color": "#ffffff",
            "text_color": "#000000",
            "accent_color": "#b45309",
            "desc_color": "#4b5563",
            "border_color": "#000000"
          }
        }
      },
