    "hc_tab_content_highlights_VprjqV": {
      "type": "hc-tab-content-highlights",
      "blocks": {
        "sweat_management_cDYgzL": {
          "type": "sweat-management",
          "settings": {
            "tag": "01 — Active Temperature Regulation",
            "heading": "Advanced Night Sweat Management",
            "description": "<p>Standard sheets trap heat against your skin, which forces your body to sweat in order to cool itself down and ultimately disrupts your sleep. The Jax Sheets address <strong>Phase Changing Materials</strong> embedded in the fabric that absorb excess heat as your body temperature rises, storing it within the material rather than letting it build up against your skin. As your temperature naturally drops through the night, the PCM releases that stored heat back gradually, keeping your thermal environment stable in both directions. By reducing the heat spikes that trigger night sweats in the first place, these sheets help you stay in the ideal thermal zone for uninterrupted rest.</p>",
            "badge_text": "NASA TECH",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "tooltip_trigger": "Phase Changing Materials",
            "tooltip_content": "<p><strong>WHAT ARE PCMS?</strong></p><p>Physically, Phase Changing Materials are specialized, plant based waxes contained within millions of microscopic bubbles embedded in the fabric. These micro capsules allow the wax to change from a solid to a liquid and back again to manage heat, all without making the fabric feel wet or heavy. Because they are part of the fiber itself, they provide a physical temperature solution that will not wash out or lose effectiveness over time.</p><p><strong>WHY ARE THEY IN THE JAX SHEETS?</strong></p><p>We use PCMs as a thermal battery to help reduce night sweats before they start. While standard sheets only react once you are already sweating, PCMs are proactive. When you get too warm, the micro capsules absorb and store your excess body heat. When you cool down, they release it back gradually. This technology was originally developed for NASA spacesuits to help protect astronauts from extreme temperature swings. In the Jax Sheets, it works the same way, helping you maintain a more stable thermal environment throughout the night for deeper, more uninterrupted sleep.</p>",
            "bg_color": "#000000",
            "text_color": "#ffffff",
            "accent_color": "#b45309",
            "desc_color": "#9ca3af"
          }
        },
        "dry_sweet_trJhV7": {
          "type": "dry-sweet",
          "settings": {
            "tag": "02 — HUMIDITY & MOISTURE CONTROL",
            "heading": "The Dry-Sleep System",
            "description": "<p>While PCM manages the heat, our embedded <strong>Volcanic Ash</strong> and <strong>Coconut Charcoal</strong> manage the humidity. These materials work to pull moisture away from your skin before it can even turn into visible sweat. By instantly evaporating skin humidity, the fabric prevents that damp, \"clammy\" feeling common with traditional bedding. This ensures your sleep environment remains dry and breathable, keeping you comfortable even in high-humidity environments or through changing seasons.</p>",
            "center_label": "Dry-Sleep",
            "vapor_label": "Vapor",
            "heat_label": "Heat",
            "badge_text": "Active Wicking",
            "schematic_footer": "Hydro-Dynamic Evaporation Schematic",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "tooltip_1_trigger": "Volcanic Ash",
            "tooltip_1_content": "<p><strong>WHAT IS VOLCANIC ASH?</strong></p><p>Volcanic ash in textiles means ultra-fine mineral particles from volcanic rock. Embedded in fibers, they create microscopic pathways that help absorb and move moisture vapor away from the skin instead of letting it sit on the surface.</p><p><strong>WHY IS IT IN JAX SHEETS?</strong></p><p>Jax Sheets weave volcanic ash into the fabric so humidity is pulled away from your body before it can feel damp or clammy. That keeps the sleep surface drier and more breathable on warm or humid nights.</p>",
            "tooltip_2_trigger": "Coconut Charcoal",
            "tooltip_2_content": "<p><strong>WHAT IS COCONUT CHARCOAL?</strong></p><p>Coconut charcoal is activated carbon made from coconut shells. Its porous structure adsorbs odor molecules and helps manage moisture in fabrics—similar to premium filters that use carbon to trap impurities at a microscopic level.</p><p><strong>WHY IS IT IN JAX SHEETS?</strong></p><p>In Jax Sheets, coconut charcoal works with the rest of the fiber system to reduce odors and balance humidity in your bedding. The result is a cleaner-smelling, less clammy sleep surface between washes.</p>",
            "tooltip_3_trigger": "",
            "tooltip_3_content": "",
            "bg_color": "#ffffff",
            "text_color": "#000000",
            "accent_color": "#b45309",
            "desc_color": "#4b5563",
            "wick_color": "#3b82f6"
          }
        },
        "steady_temperature_speed_74JHc6": {
          "type": "steady-temperature-speed",
          "settings": {
            "section_id": "steady-temperature-fir",
            "tag": "03 — FIR Bio-Ceramic Technology",
            "heading": "Steady-Temperature Sleep",
            "description": "<p>Most bedding is passive, it either traps heat or lets it escape. The <strong>FIR Bio-Ceramics</strong> in the Jax Sheets actively work with your body's natural heat output, re-emitting it as far infrared energy that encourages circulation and helps your body regulate its own temperature more efficiently through the night. The result is fewer of those subtle temperature fluctuations that pull you out of deep sleep without you ever realizing why.</p>",
            "center_label": "FIR",
            "body_heat_label": "Body Heat",
            "reflected_label": "Reflected Energy",
            "badge_text": "Bio-Active",
            "schematic_footer": "Thermal Mirror Schematic",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "tooltip_1_trigger": "FIR Bio-Ceramics",
            "tooltip_1_content": "<p><strong>WHAT ARE THEY?</strong></p><p>Physically, FIR (Far Infrared) Bio-Ceramics are a blend of naturally occurring, heat-reactive minerals that are ground into a fine powder and permanently infused into the fabric fibers. They are \"bio-active,\" meaning they are designed to interact specifically with the heat emitted by the human body.</p><p><strong>WHY ARE THEY IN JAX SHEETS?</strong></p><p>We included Bio-Ceramics to help your body maintain a steady internal balance. While standard bedding is passive, Bio-Ceramics are active; they recycle your body's energy to stabilize your temperature and encourage better circulation. This helps you fall asleep faster and stay in \"Deep Sleep\" longer by preventing the temperature fluctuations that disrupt your rest.</p>",
            "bg_color": "#000000",
            "text_color": "#ffffff",
            "accent_color": "#b45309",
            "desc_color": "#9ca3af",
            "energy_color": "#ef4444",
            "heat_arrow_color": "#fb923c"
          }
        }
      },
