          "settings": {
            "tag": "02 — Structural Integrity",
            "heading": "built to last",
            "description": "<p>Durability in bedding isn't just about thickness; it’s about how the fibers handle the physical stress of sleep and maintenance. Jax Sheets are built with a resilient HercLeón™ structure engineered to resist stretching, sagging, and pilling, even with constant nightly use. Our fibers are designed to maintain their integrity under tension and snap back instead of breaking down, staying smooth rather than fraying over time. This structural stability ensures your sheets stay crisp, hold their fit on the mattress, and maintain that \"new sheet\" feel significantly longer than traditional fabrics.</p>",
