          "type": "hc-honest-truth",
          "settings": {
            "eyebrow": "Transparency",
            "heading": "The Honest Truth",
            "lead": "We're not for everyone. Here's why you might NOT want to buy from us.",
            "card_1_num": "01",
            "card_1_title": "Jax Sheets Aren't Cheap",
            "card_1_body": "They cost more than most people expect - and that's fair. Every fiber and finish was chosen for performance, longevity, and health, not price. Yes, it's a higher upfront cost - but Jax Sheets are designed to last 5-10 years while staying soft, cool, and clean. Over time, they end up costing less than replacing cheaper sheets every year.",
            "card_2_num": "02",
            "card_2_title": "Oil Stains Can Happen",
            "card_2_body": "Jax Sheets are highly absorbent - that's part of what makes them breathable - but it also means they can hold onto oil from skin, hair, or skincare a bit more than cotton. Luckily, they wash out easily with proper care, and Jax 2.0 handles this better than ever but still not perfect.",
            "card_3_num": "03",
            "card_3_title": "They Need Some Care When Washing",
            "card_3_body": "Jax Sheets are performance fabrics, not indestructible gym towels. Avoid harsh soaps, bleach, fabric softeners and rough loads with jeans or zippers. Treat them right and they'll last up to a decade - ignore them and they'll last a few years.",
            "card_4_num": "04",
            "card_4_title": "They might feel different than what you're used to",
            "card_4_body": "They don't feel like crisp cotton or slick silk - they're somewhere in between. Some people love that balance of smoothness and breathability; others prefer something more traditional.",
            "card_5_num": "05",
            "card_5_title": "You Might Start Disliking Every Other Bed Sheet You Sleep In",
            "card_5_body": "We once had a customer who lost his set of Jax Sheets in his divorce and others who plan their laundry day around being able to put Jax back on their bed, so you've been warned. Jax Sheets will ruin other sheets for you.",
            "closing_brand": "HercLeon",
            "closing_tagline": "Built for the 1% who demand more.",
            "bg_color": "#ffffff",
            "text_color": "#000000",
            "accent_color": "#B45309",
            "muted_color": "#4b5563",
            "grid_line_color": "#000000",
            "card_hover_bg": "#f9fafb",
            "aside_bg": "#f9fafb",
            "aside_muted_color": "#9ca3af"
          }
        }
      },
